    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "That <code>QueryParserUtil</code> class I mentioned in my comments is not for the classic query parser. It is for the query parser your question is discussing. The &quot;classic&quot; query parser has its own separate <a href=\"https://lucene.apache.org/core/10_2_2/queryparser/org/apache/lucene/queryparser/classic/QueryParserBase.html#escape(java.lang.String)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>escape()</code></a> method, also. Note how that is in the <code>org.apache.lucene.queryparser.classic</code> package. The <code>escape()</code> method in my earlier comments is in the <code>org.apache.lucene.queryparser.flexible.standard</code> package. Note the difference between &quot;classic&quot; and &quot;standard&quot;."
