  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/79752730/what-special-characters-does-lucene-standardqueryparser-use",
  "title" : "What special characters does Lucene StandardQueryParser use?",
  "body" : "<p>When user strings are submitted to Lucene's <code>StandardQueryParser.parse</code>, the parser will sometimes throw an exception because the string includes special characters in unexpected ways (e.g. search for &quot;Wham!&quot;).</p>\n<p>Lucene documented the list of special characters for the old <code>QueryParser</code>. But the new, preferred <code>StandardQueryParser</code> includes some new special characters, such as <code>=</code>.</p>\n<p>What are these characters? Are they documented anywhere? (I have not been able to locate any comprehensive list.) I would like to simply remove such characters from queries that cause parse exceptions (not all users can be expected to submit well-formed queries in the wild).</p>\n<p>To reiterate, <em>I am asking about StandardQueryParser not QueryParser</em>.</p>\n"
